Log in with username: ./nolop-machine
Click the icon at the bottom of the screen. If you don't have an Adobe account, you can make one

so stick with those if you can.

Step 4: put your file in RGB mode
Step 5: set the colors of all your lines
Step 6: Print your file to the printer called VLS3.60/75
The laser can cut most wood, plastic, leather, and rubber up to a thickness of around 3 mm. Our
laser is not powerful enough to cut metal. The bed of the laser is 300 x 600 mm, or around 12
inches x 24 inches. The Nolop store sells 3 mm plywood and acrylic precut to the dimensions of
the bed.
Select the lines you want to cut and double-click the stroke icon to open the color picker.
Select File > Document Color Mode > RGB Color. This will allow you to use colors as a code to tell
the laser what cut style to use.
Step 7: start the print
Check that your print is starting properly. The heated printbed takes 2-3 minutes to warm up. You
after that, you can leave it printing unattended.
For cuts, your red lines of width 0.001 inches should be barely visible in Illustrator.
Hit Ctrl-P to print in Illustrator. You should not need to change any settings. Illustrator will foolishly
believe that it is printing to a conventional paper printer, but really, the laser driver will take over!

FAQ

tspan.tspan: Why not leave the laser unattended?

text.tspan: Sometimes, the laser sets your material on fire. We have a fire blanket on the side of each laser,
which works great, if you are there to detect the fire. The blanket will not deploy itself.

tspan.tspan: What if I need to cut something really thick or really big?
